          <p class='first-para'>
            I praise what the Conservatives have done in the past, particularly John Major, who was
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_281wh' title='Col. 281WH &mdash; HC Deb 10 July 2002 vol 388 c281WH' name='column_281wh' href='#column_281wh' rel='bookmark'>281WH</a>
            instrumental in the current process. However, I was concerned earlier this year when I understood that the Conservatives were pulling out of the cross-party agreement. They sound as if they are now on board, for which I have unequivocal praise.
          </p>
